entry.title: Serialize and compute non-finite color channels
entry.content:
http://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/8629

http://github.com/web-platform-tests/wpt/pull/39137/files

http://wpt.fyi/results/css/css-color/parsing



Color parsing is a part of Interop 2023. Handling non-finite inputs

to color channels is a bit tricky. At parse time `calc(NaN)` and

`calc(infinity)` (and their equivalents) are valid CSS numerical inputs,

and should get re-serialized as such so that they round-trip.



Per-spec, `calc(NaN)` should become 0 at computed value time.

`calc(infinity)` should remain `calc(infinity)`, except in cases where it represents a clamped color channel, such as lightness or chroma.

Unfortunately, blink had previously made no distinction between parsed

and computed colors, hence the creation of

blink::Color::ResolveNonFiniteValues (called from

TextLinkColors::ColorFromCSSValue) in this CL.



Before CSS Color 4, color functions were less exposed to things like

`calc` functions, so this problem went unnoticed.

entry.title: Multiplanar: Reland Plumb color space through D3D11TextureWrapper
entry.content:
Previous patch had issue with passing the correct color space when

creating texture wrapper as there can be fallback to config color

space when calling ProcessTexture in CreatePictureBuffers. Updated to

set to that if picture color space is invalid.



Original Description:

This change plumbs the video frame color space to D3D11TextureWrapper

where it is used for creating a shared image. This is needed for

multiplanar shared images where the color space within the shared image

is used to create skia images and then perform a YUV to RGB conversion

within RasterDecoder through a skia blit instead of earlier plumbing

the video frame color space to perform conversion through another

method.



Here, the color space is passed from the D3D11 video decoder which

also clears the picture buffers, recreating pictures and shared images

on a color space change trigger. The color space is then passed through

the texture selector to wrapper where it is stored and used for

creating shared images later.

entry.title: [ios] Decrease unnecessary test dependencies on settings sync promo
entry.content:
Test-only change.

Many tests don't care about this promo specifically, but use it as a

way to sign the user in, or verify that the user is signed-out. The

promo will be removed in future CLs, so we need to get rid of such

dependencies. The promo itself still has test coverage in

SigninSettingsTestCase.



To remove the unnecessary dependencies, we use 2 different strategies:



1. Callers of [SigninEarlGreyUI signinWithFakeIdentity] -> Just change

the method's implementation to sign-in via Recent Tabs instead, since

callers don't make assumptions about the sign-in entry point.



2. Tests that directly manipulate the "Continue as..." and "Choose

another account" buttons in the promo, i.e. PrimarySignInButton() and

SecondarySigninButton() -> Suppress the promo by increasing its

impression count and adapt tests to use the "Turn On Sync" row instead.



In 2, some tests could be refactored not to depend on the entry point,

and then do something similar to 1, but that would require more effort.



Note: PrimarySignInButton() and SecondarySigninButton() are still used

for other promo entry points, so it doesn't make sense to change their

implementation.

entry.title: [ash] Fix DragWindowController window opacity race condition
entry.content:
Currently there exists a race condition in ash / wm code that can

result in a window drag finishing with an invisible window. This

race is represented disproportionately for lacros window drag

sessions.



The problematic sequence of events is as follows:



1. Create a maximized window with two tabs and have two displays

side-by-side.

2. Start dragging one of the tabs out of the window and onto the

second display. Drop the tab into the second display.

3. This initiates a call to SetBoundsDirectCrossFade() in response

to a maximize state change [1].

4. This calls into CrossFadeAnimationInternal().

a. This sets the new layer's opacity immediately to 0 [2].

b. After this it begins to animate the new layer's opacity to

1 with a non-zero animation duration [3].

Note: However this does not happen immediately, it requires

time for the animation to complete.

5. Before the animation to an opacity of 1 has completed we can

immediately attempt to begin the drag, which will latch the

transparent layer opacity [4].

6. When the window is later dropped the window will revert to this

latched opacity [5].



To avoid races that can result from drag events and animation

resolution time DragWindowController has been updated to latch

the target opacity, which eliminates the need to worry about

animation resolution.



[1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:ash/wm/default_state.cc;l=680;drc=1fbf0109061744c27d30d7312659e2829ef603f7



[2] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/refs/heads/main:ash/wm/window_animations.cc;l=354;drc=5992439d25f71ce29efa8db1c699b99e8773d41f



[3] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/refs/heads/main:ash/wm/window_animations.cc;l=380;drc=5992439d25f71ce29efa8db1c699b99e8773d41f



[4] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:ash/wm/drag_window_controller.cc;l=169;drc=7cbf53e8f2ef6447b75715fb8109022a02b1353d



[5] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:ash/wm/drag_window_controller.cc;l=183;drc=7cbf53e8f2ef6447b75715fb8109022a02b1353d

entry.title: Generate stdlib GN rules from the Rust src tree when rolling Rust
entry.content:
Reland of https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/4569316



This avoids the need to:

1. Build gnrt locally

2. Then download the roll CL

3. Copy Rust packages to prod

4. gclient sync

5. Run `gnrt gen --for-std`

6. Reupload the CL



In order to have the Rust roll pass the trybots.



upload_revision.py will, when rolling rust, do the `cargo vendor`

step in the Rust git checkout to get its dependencies, install

cargo and rustc in a sysroot, build `gnrt` using cargo, and then

run `gnrt gen --for-std=third_party/rust_src/src` which regenerates

the GN rules for the Rust stdlib from the updated version of Rust.



Previously gnrt gen --for-std would generate rules from the Rust

library found in //third_party/rust-toolchain, but that requires

Rust to already be rolled, so this now uses the feature of specifying

the Rust source tree root to --for-std.



Bug: 1401042, 1451335

entry.title: Re-enable LaunchingAppThatRequiresNetworkWhilstOfflineShouldShowNetworkScreen
entry.content:
This test flakily failed at the WaitForOobeScreen step, because we jumped straight into the network screen instead of holding on the splash screen for 10 seconds as expected.



The reason we jumped straight into the network screen is the following callpath happening during installation:

NetworkUiController::InitializeNetwork

-> AppLaunchSplashScreenHandler::UpdateAppLaunchState

-> NetworkUiController::OnNetworkStateChanged

-> KioskLaunchController::OnNetworkLost

-> NetworkUiController::OnNetworkLostDuringInstallation

-> NetworkUiController::ShowNetworkConfigureUI.



This was fixed by https://crrev.com/c/4583229 by blocking the call from AppLaunchSplashScreenHandler::UpdateAppLaunchState to NetworkUiController::OnNetworkStateChanged.

entry.title: Use identity scale for filters_scale in RendererPixelTests
entry.content:
The filter scale and origin parameters to the RPDQ are used to directly

define the local matrix the image filters are evaluated with. Using a

default-constructed gfx::Vector2dF has a (0,0) scale factor so the

local matrix is the zero matrix and not invertible.



This went undetected previously because color filters don't have any

geometric parameters affected by the local matrix, so the zero matrix was being silently ignored. A skia-side change is making

`makeWithLocalMatrix()` return null if the matrix is not invertible,

so this updates the tests to use an identity value.

entry.title: [Layout] Fix DCHECK when updating visible tab IDs
entry.content:
Fix a DCHECK in tab_content_manager.cc related to the ThumbnailCacheRefactor [1]. The DCHECK is triggered during

SimpleAnimationLayout if a StaticLayout attempts to invoke

TabContentManager#updateVisibleTabIds while the SimpleAnimationLayout

is active. This happens because StaticLayout updates the visible tab

IDs both when it is shown and when a tab becomes selected (to cover

the scenario where it is already visible). This is incorrect as the

active layout is the only one that should be able to

call updateVisibleTabIds otherwise other layouts might become broken.



Prevent this by filtering Layout#updateCacheVisibleIds{AndPrimary} to

only be called when the StaticLayout is active. Also add an assert to

catch and correct any other instances of this.



This is not a problem for StaticLayout as it updates the visible

tab IDs during show() as well.



Also properly override Layout#setTabModelSelector in StaticLayout. It

is unclear why this was an intentional no-op it does not appear to

cause issues by overriding it and dates back to the great upstreaming in

2015.



[1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:chrome/browser/android/compositor/tab_content_manager.cc;drc=e502291081d7e28f852b0ac8486449d7a1c509e1;l=185

entry.title: [//media][Mac] Eliminate PictureInfo taking in client/service texture ID
entry.content:
VtVideoDecodeAccelerator's PictureInfo struct has two constructors:

- One that is empty and signifies that the accelerator should use

SharedImage

- One that takes in a client/service texture ID and specifies that the

accelerator should *not* use SharedImage



Following the elimination of the NaCL use case and subsequent

refactorings, the codepath that invokes PictureInfo() with a

client/service texture ID is never actually invoked: the client/service

texture ID come from a PictureBuffer instance created by

PictureBufferManager::CreatePictureBuffers(), which now creates only

PictureBuffers with empty client/service texture IDs on Mac. This CL

replaces the codepath that creates a PictureInfo with a client/service

tetxure ID with a CHECK that the PictureBuffer's client/service texture

ID are empty.



A followup CL will eliminate all of the non-SharedImage code in

vt_video_video_decode_accelerator_mac.*, which is now dead.

entry.title: Measure fetch keepalive requests after context is detached
entry.content:
This CL adds the following UMA logging:



- `Blink.Fetch.KeepAlive.Total`: a single bucket UMA to count total

fetch keepalive requests made.

- `Blink.Fetch.KeepAlive.Total.IsSuccess` a two-bucket UMA to count

success/fail loads of fetch keepalive requests.

- `Blink.Fetch.KeepAlive.AfterDetached.IsSuccess` a two-bucket UMA to

count success/fail loads of fetch keepalive requests **after the

context is detached**.

- `Blink.Fetch.KeepAlive.AfterDetached.Duration`: estimate how long a

keepalive request stays after the context is gone.



Bug: 1356128
